race.description: Buy An Arrowfield Graduate Maiden Plate
race.comment: LADY OF THE CASTLE (11) started favourite but gave away too much start on debut last time out over 1100m at Gosford, clocking in an eye-catching second. Maps nicely - watch for another big finish on this longer run home. DOUBLE VISION (5) is an interesting debutante from the Waterhouse/Bott yard. At the races for the first time as a four-year-old. Has trialled twice and won both so there is obviously some talent there. Keep a close watch on the betting. INDIGO STAR (1) was hard to miss first-up at the Beaumont track, rattling home into second at the end of 1200m. A little surprised to see Waller drop him back a shade in trip but trust the premier trainer and James McDonald who has taken the ride. KITESURFING (10) had a few things go against her first-up at Canterbury in a run that may be worth overlooking. Freshened up and showed enough on debut last prep to suggest she can be competitive. LET'S GO BARBIE (6) is a chance second-up from an extended break. Respect GORGEOUS (9) on debut.
